This paper is about neural machine translation (NMT), which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also introduces novel applications of the factored output architecture, which involves the use of auxiliary prediction tasks, and this could potentially be relevant to other areas of machine learning such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of subword units, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) for image segmentation and object recognition.
